column9: Donor: The Taipei Representative Office in the UK (TRO)

The Royal United Services Institute paid for flights with a value of £3,343.27 in order for me to attend and speak at a conference in Chicago from 28 to 30 March 2012.  Address of payer: Whitehall
, 
London
, 
SW1A 2ET
, The Chicago Council on Global Affairs paid for my accommodation, transfers and meals, value £583. Address: 332 South Michigan Avenue, Suite 110 D, Chicago, Illinois 60604-4416, USA. Both organisations were among the organisers and supporters of the conference. Hours: 3 days. No fee was paid. (Registered 18 April 2012)
